The European Community (EC) is to boostspending to help the jobless this year.    The EC's executive commission said in a statement spendingon its so-called social fund would rise to 3.1 billion EuropeanCurrency Units from 2.5 billion ECUs in 1986. The fund isdesigned to help boost job creation and improve workermobility, and supplement national schemes in the EC's 12 memberstates.    Another 60 mln ECUs could be added if EC ministers switchunused project credits to other programs, the Commission said.    Italy is the largest net beneficiary in 1987, getting 635mln ECUs, with Britain in second place with 580 mln. REUTER&#3;